result.execSummary:
All charges against Ashley N. Bird in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Ashley N. Bird is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 11:07 AM Defendant Ashley N. Bird in court, in custody.  Attorney Ian Mickelson in court for Ashley N. Bird.  Attorney Curtis E Johnson in court for State of Wisconsin. State moves for dismissal of case, so ordered.

2:01 PM Defendant Ashley N. Bird appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Ian Mickelson in court for Ashley N. Bird.  Attorney Curtis E Johnson in court for State of Wisconsin.  Court makes disclosure in re. recusal; parties waive request for recusal.    PLEAS:  09/07/2022 @ 11:00 am.
Plea/sentencing hearing on September 7, 2022 at 11:00 am.

10:17 AM - Attorney Curtis E Johnson in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Ian Mickelson in court for Ashley N. Bird.  Ashley Bird appears in person in custody.  Ct. hears from Atty. Mickelson and presents completed waiver of preliminary form to Court,  Waiver of Preliminary Hearing - colloquy given.  Defendant freely, willingly, knowledgeably and intelligently waives right to preliminary hearing.  Information to be filed by ADA Johnson.  Atty. Mickelson would like to proceed with arraignment.  Court advised defendant of the charge and penalty.  Defendant stood mute.  Court entered plea of not guilty and set matter for status conference on 9/2/2022 at 2:00 p.m.  Ms. Bird remanded back to Iowa Co. Jail.
Status conference scheduled for September 2, 2022 at 02:00 pm.
Status conference on September 2, 2022 at 02:00 pm.
Preliminary Hearing on August 18, 2022 at 10:15 am.

1:15 PM Defendant Ashley N. Bird appeared by video from the Iowa County Jail.  Attorney Curtis E Johnson in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Ian Mickelson in court for Ashley N. Bird. Court confirms Ms. Bird's home address.  Attorney Mickelson waives formal reading of Complaint and requests date for a preliminary hearing.  Court sets matter for PH on 8/18/2022 at 10:15 a.m.  No objection from the State or defense counsel to Court Commissioner Reimann presiding at the PH.   Attorney Mickelson addresses court regarding motion for bond modification and requests a signature bond or lower cash bond.  Court hears from ADA Johnson, who opposes any modification of the current bond.  Court denied motion for bond modification.  Matter adjourned.
Preliminary Hearing scheduled for August 18, 2022 at 10:15 am.
